Package seng202.team4.controller

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AirlineTabController
    Performs logic for the 'Airline' tab of the application Responsible for connecting the airline data to the JavaFX interface, this includes displaying the airlines in the JavaFX TableView with data from the 'Airlines' SQLite database table and also initialising/updating the additive filtering and searching of said data.
    AirportTabController
    Performs logic for the 'Airport' tab of the application Responsible for connecting the airport data to the JavaFX interface, this includes displaying the airports in the JavaFX TableView with data from the 'Airports' SQLite database table and also initialising/updating the additive filtering and searching of said data.
    ContributionsGraphController
    Performs the logic for generating a visualization for the contribution of each selected route to the users overall carbon footprint.
    DataController
    Describes the required functionality of all the controllers that display tables of data in their scene.
    EmissionsTabController
    Performs logic for the 'Emissions' tab of the application Responsible for connecting the selected route data to the JavaFX interface, this includes displaying the selected routes in the JavaFX TableView with data from the 'RoutesSelected' SQLite database table and also using a search filter on this data.
    ErrorController
    Controls the operation of the changeable error popup.
    FileUploadController
    Controller used for uploading datasets to the application.
    FlightPathTabController
    Performs logic for the 'Flight Path' tab of the application Responsible for connecting the flight path data to the JavaFX interface, this includes displaying the coordinates and altitude in the JavaFX TableView with data from the 'FlightPath' SQLite database table and also initialising/updating the additive filtering and searching of said data.
    HomePageController
    Performs logic for the 'Home' tab of the application Responsible for giving instructions to the user and in a later release will be responsible for global searching functionality.
    InvalidLinesPopUpController
    Controls the behaviour of the invalid lines pop up when the user uploads a file with invalid lines
    MapTabController
    Performs the logic for the 'Map' tab of the application.
    NewAirline
    Describes the functionality required for getting a new airline record.
    NewAirport
    Describes the functionality required for getting a new airport record.
    NewFlightPath
    Describes the functionality required for getting a new flight path record.
    NewRecord
    Abstract class defining common functionality between the controllers used for adding new records.
    NewRoute
    Describes the functionality required for getting a new route record.
    RouteTabController
    Performs logic for the 'Routes' tab of the application; extends the DataController Class.
